# Inventory Service — API examples
# Use with VS Code REST Client, IntelliJ HTTP Client, or similar.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1

### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Create product
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "SKU-DEMO",
  "name": "Demo Widget",
  "quantity_on_hand": 100
}

### List products
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?limit=10&offset=0

### Low stock
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/low-stock?threshold=10

### Record RESTOCK
POST {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}/movements
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: restock-demo-001

{
  "movement_type": "RESTOCK",
  "quantity": 50
}

### Record SALE
POST {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}/movements
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "movement_type": "SALE",
  "quantity": 5
}

### Record ADJUSTMENT
POST {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}/movements
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "movement_type": "ADJUSTMENT",
  "quantity": -2,
  "reason": "Damaged units removed"
}

### Movement history
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}/movements?limit=20

### Movement summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}/movements/summary
